{
  "title": "Fluffy Middle Eastern Padron Pepper Skewers",
  "description": "Tender padron peppers cooked sous‑vide then seared, served with a light tahini‑lemon sauce and fragrant spices for a midnight‑craving, sugar‑free Middle Eastern dish.",
  "cuisine": "Middle Eastern",
  "diet": [
    "vegan",
    "gluten-free",
    "sugar-free"
  ],
  "meal": "dinner",
  "ingredients": [
    {
      "name": "Padron peppers",
      "amount": "12 medium"
    },
    {
      "name": "Olive oil",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Garlic cloves",
      "amount": "3, minced"
    },
    {
      "name": "Lemon",
      "amount": "1, zest 1, juice 2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Tahini",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "Water",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sumac",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Za'atar",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh mint leaves",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons, chopped"
    },
    {
      "name": "Chopped parsley",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": "optional garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Thread the padron peppers onto 8‑inch bamboo skewers, brushing each with olive oil and sprinkling with salt.",
    "Pack the skewers into a vacuum‑seal bag, seal, and sous‑vide at 68 °C (154 °F) for 45 minutes.",
    "After the sous‑vide, remove the skewers, pat dry, and sear on a preheated grill or grill pan for 2 minutes per side until a slight char forms.",
    "While the peppers grill, whisk together tahini, lemon juice, minced garlic, water, sumac, and za'atar until smooth.",
    "Serve the hot skewers drizzled with the tahini sauce, garnished with chopped mint and parsley, and a sprinkle of extra sumac if desired."
  ],
